## 🔬 Technical Highlights

### 1. EAC Formula Implementation
```csharp
public static CategoryCost Calculate(Money planned, Money actual)
{
    var projected = actual.Amount > planned.Amount ? actual : planned; // MAX
    var variance = actual.Subtract(planned);
    return new CategoryCost(planned, actual, projected, variance);
}
```

### 2. Money Value Object (Full Arithmetic)
```csharp
public record Money(decimal Amount, string Currency)
{
    public Money Add(Money other) { ValidateCurrency(other); return new(Amount + other.Amount, Currency); }
    public Money Subtract(Money other) { ValidateCurrency(other); return new(Amount - other.Amount, Currency); }
    public Money Multiply(decimal multiplier) => new(Amount * multiplier, Currency);
    public static Money operator +(Money left, Money right) => left.Add(right);
}
```

### 3. Caching Strategy
```csharp
return await _cache.GetOrCreateAsync(cacheKey, async entry =>
{
    entry.AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5);
    var calculation = await _calculationService.CalculateAsync(...);
    return MapToDto(calculation);
});
```

### 4. Domain Event Pattern
```csharp
public void Create(...)
{
    var adjustment = new CostAdjustment { ... };
    adjustment.AddDomainEvent(new CostAdjustmentCreatedEvent(...));
    return adjustment;
}
```

